antiterrorism expert says there was no evidence libyan planned to 
arm terrorists with chemicals but reason to fear it might they 
have no record of restraint he says 
nov 25 a libyan official tells italy his country adheres to 
international prohibitions on the use of chemicals weapons those 
prohibitions do not cover manufacture or ownership 
dec 19 the state department says libya is on the verge of 
fullscale production and calls on all countries to deny related 
technology to libya iran and iraq 
