keebler co said today it will eliminate 
tropical oils and lard from its cookies and crackers to reduce 
cholesterol 
the company also said it would begin listing nutritional values 
on its packages 
keebler snacks made without tropical oils and lard should begin 
appearing on shelves in march said thomas garvin president and 
chief executive officer 
tropical oils are heavy in saturated fats which can be converted 
by the body into arteryblocking cholesterol lard is high in 
cholesterol 
by the end of 1989 no keebler product will contain coconut oil 
palm oil palm kernel oil lard or beef fat said keebler spokesman 
stuart greenblatt they will be replaced with vegetable oil lower in 
saturated fat he said 
butter and cheese both of which contain fat will be used in 
some products he said 
weve been working on the reformulation for more than a year 
garvin said were extremely proud to respond to consumer concerns 
about these ingredients by replacing them with more healthful oils 
greenblatt would not disclose the cost of reformulating the 
products but said the decision would not affect prices 
under the new labeling keebler products will show the number of 
calories and amount of protein carbohydrates vitamins sodium 
cholesterol and other nutritional categories per serving greenblatt 
said 
